<item>
            <title>[LU-5991] memory leak on mount failure</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5991</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;lustre_fill_super() allocates lsi and assumes that in case of failures server_fill_super() or ll_fill_super() will call server_put_super()/ll_put_super() to free the lsi. However,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;server_fill_super() misses that when lsi_prepare() fails.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ll_fill_super() misses that when OBD_ALLOC_PTR(cfg) or&lt;br/&gt;
  ll_init_sbi() fail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
